3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design of distributed space time codes for cooperative networks, which can be viewed as a control problem in the context of wireless communication systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of space time codes for improving the reliability of wireless communication, which is a topic relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography or security, but the design of space time codes can have implications for the security of wireless communication systems.
